SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04952488
Version: 1

HPSBOV03540 rev.1 - HPE OpenVMS TCPIP Bind Services and OpenVMS TCPIP IPC
Services for OpenVMS, Remote Disclosure of Information, Execution of Code,
Denial of Service (DoS)

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2016-01-28
Last Updated: 2016-01-28

Potential Security Impact: Remote Code Execution, Denial of Service (DoS),
Disclosure of Information

Source: Hewlett Packard Enterprise, Product Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
Potential security vulnerabilities have been identified with the OpenVMS
TCPIP Bind Services and OpenVMS TCPIP IPC Services for OpenVMS. These
vulnerabilities could be exploited remotely resulting in execution of code
with the privileges of Bind, disclosure of information, or cause a Denial of
Service (DoS).

References:

  - CVE-2007-0493
  - CVE-2007-0494
  - CVE-2012-1667
  - CVE-2012-5166
  - CVE-2012-4244
  - CVE-2009-4022
  - CVE-2010-0097
  - CVE-2008-0122
  - PSRT110022

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP OpenVMS TCPIP Services V 5.7 ECO5 BIND

BACKGROUND

